<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb7d92007-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s807"><num value="807">§ 807.</num><heading> Exemption for monetary policy</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall apply to rules that concern monetary policy proposed or implemented by the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System or the Federal Open Market Committee.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb7d92008-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/121/tII/s251">Pub. L. 104–121, title II, § 251</ref>, <date date="1996-03-29">Mar. 29, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/874">110 Stat. 874</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
